<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870709-0080 </DOCNO><HL> Hills Stores Sells DebtAnd Stock in Initial Offer</HL><DD> 07/09/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> HDSBOND MARKET NEWS (BON)INITIAL STOCK OFFERINGS (INI)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><DATELINE> CANTON, Mass.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hills Department Stores Inc. sold 3,675,000 common shares at $11 each in its initial public offering. It also offered $40 million of 8 3/4% junior subordinated debentures, due 2002 and priced at par, Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc., chief underwriter, said.    Drexel said 3,175,000 shares were sold to the public and the rest were sold to Thomas H. Lee, a company director. The company sold all of the shares. The debentures are convertible at a rate of $14 of debentures for each common share.    Hills plans to use the proceeds, along with bank borrowings, to purchase its preferred stock and redeem preferred shares of its principal unit, Hills Stores Cos.    Hills operates 139 discount department stores in the U.S. In composite trading yesterday on the New York Stock Exchange, Hills common closed at $11.50. </TEXT></DOC>